ref-7-9                    Xerox Quintus Prolog Reference Manual                    Section 7-9: arg(+ArgNum, +Term, -Arg)arg(ArgNum, Term, Arg) unifies Arg with the ArgNumth argument of term Term.Initially, ArgNum must be instantiated to a positive integer and Term to acompound term.  The arguments are numbered from 1 upwards.  For example:              | ?- arg(2, foo(a,b,c), X).            X = barg(ArgNum, Term, Arg) has no associated error conditions.